  "texts": [
    "They validated the model using two different protein structures, HIV-1 transactivation response element RNA and ATP-aptamer structures.",
    "The model showed an AUROC of ca. 0.87.",
    "In 2020, Simonovsky and Meyers proposed a CNN-based model called 'DeeplyTough' for pocket matching (Simonovsky and Meyers 2020).",
    "The model can convert the 3-D representation of a protein pocket into descriptor vectors.",
    "These vectors are then used for comparing ligand binding pockets on protein by calculating pairwise Euclidean distances."
  ],
